2. 'I'he Flora of Rodalsberg.

The stratigraphical position of the plant-bearing bed at Rodalsberg may be seen from the Section given in text-fig. 1 (p. 4). It is considerably higher up in the series than the plant-bed at Munka Tagarp, but it lies probably a long dis- tance below the Cardimn-bed. The plant-bearing rock is a rust-coloured, fairly fine-grained sandstone, which occurs in close connection with a thin seam of poor coal. The plant- remains occur as impressions‚ without any trace of the vege- table tissue. On account of the fract-ured state of the rock, they are very fragmentary and, moreover‚ not very distinct as a rule. The material, which has been collected by MOBERG‚ will be described below.
